          "reviewRating": {
            "@type": "Rating",
            "ratingValue": "1",
            "bestRating": "5",
            "worstRating": "1"
          },
          "reviewBody": "I recently visited to inquire about admissions for first grade, and I was disappointed by the experience. A month prior, I had called the school and was told admissions were open, but the enquiry form had to be filled out in person. When we arrived, the front office staff only asked for basic details (name and date of birth) and then handed me a paper. I expected an enquiry or admission form, but instead, the paper stated there was no current vacancy and that we would only be contacted if a request letter was submitted with specific details like parent’s names, occupations, and reasons for wanting admission.\nWhen I asked for clarification, the staff's response was incredibly rude. One even said, “Can’t you read the letter? Do whatever is given in that,” which was both unprofessional and dismissive. This behavior was surprising for a school with a 25-year history. The lack of transparency and courtesy in the admission process was shocking, especially compared to other schools, even smaller kindergartens, which have clear and welcoming processes.\nOverall, I found the admission experience at to be frustrating and discourteous.",
          "publisher": {
            "@type": "Organization",
            "name": "Yellow Slate"
          }
